<subSubSection id="0088FE2F511401DFF2595E4AE524F8EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="22A2674CF58EBE348EC71D652AA737FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25803156808341D8D265F9713B943277" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The taxonomic circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="9DEF703C5958D6079309386D1CEB61C2" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="F8C667CF23A15D70B5B8D6EC589D1D4B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is greatly impaired by the lack of knowledge of the current whereabouts of the type material of several of its associated synonyms. Types for the names 
<taxonomicName id="5A7E257AC72127E37CCDA5C6C501087A" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="5952A6EE872977118058433878029FA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09DFF84BA5AB8C699352296C00F67EEE" genus="X." lsidName="X. fockeanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="fockeanum">
<emphasis id="45B776E414E3E2DF9BD17285AC476DE7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. fockeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were successfully located and designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="CD7879B96FB0D0FF3D2188884D7164B9" author="Maas, PJM" journalOrPublisher="Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B27" refString="Maas, PJM, Maas-van de Kamer, H, 1993. Haemodoraceae. Fl. Neotropica 61: 1 - 44" title="Haemodoraceae. Fl." volume="61" year="1993">Maas and Maas-van de Kamer (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, while types for the names 
<taxonomicName id="5CB005DB5B3DEC956C66EFB0C75DCAC6" genus="X." lsidName="X. rubrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rubrum">
<emphasis id="798C829E17534FFFF882500760CD94A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rubrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E4434B3E9FA5CA7748D3E867D80C7B8F" authority="Willd. ex Baker, 1876" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Eccremis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Viridiplantae" lsidName="Eccremis scabra" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Streptophyta" rank="species" species="scabra">
<emphasis id="1E6964858DBE1C5AB9BD8D8931C338CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Eccremis scabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1E7A232B76653833FFBAE20CE2729C81" authorityName="Boeckeler" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Boeckeler" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Tympanidaceae" genus="Durandia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Durandia macrophylla" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis id="975E3BC65F083762A216DBDBFC148550" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Durandia macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were located by us and had lectotypes designated when necessary. Nonetheless, we have been unable to locate a type specimen, or illustration for 
<taxonomicName id="095A5006AC8C81A3FCBC9FE02CF524FE" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="84F2CC7037E9DB12B18B9A91ADCF72BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which prevents us from knowing if this name matches any of the 
<taxonomicName id="D08D1D18CA408AB8F474A8D5438CBCC2" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="35E3DA69EAE3265BB93E2F9CF297B566" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphs recognised by us.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A8C133FF1C6827099CB2E8FC38714346" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="A83F69615A2F739B52F2ED810BCA402C" author="Maas, PJM" journalOrPublisher="Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B27" refString="Maas, PJM, Maas-van de Kamer, H, 1993. Haemodoraceae. Fl. Neotropica 61: 1 - 44" title="Haemodoraceae. Fl." volume="61" year="1993">Maas and Maas-van de Kamer (1993)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously designated plate 66 from 
<bibRefCitation id="342C35703335B566714951250AD1E0AD" author="Lindley, J" journalOrPublisher=", Leipzig, London, Milano &amp; New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Lindley, J, 1846. New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." title="New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." year="1846">Lindley (1846)</bibRefCitation>
as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="628A6D824C097C9FB8029F72E18E0316" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="F0D8A84D1A98A58E3B7D0D145C24CEB2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The indicated plate actually depicts 
<taxonomicName id="9A3ECDCBBA9C143DEB1D9A302313244B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Swainsona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Swainsona greyana" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="greyana">
<emphasis id="625E3BEE99643FC8A8A0F3D5FDF8A6D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Swainsona greyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lindl. (
<taxonomicName id="1875B7EE1A342AA528788DB5A93D76DD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Swainsona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) and obviously cannot be the type for 
<taxonomicName id="755732E2844D7E8A789D61D3DBEDCAC9" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="DB616676CF8EE8D16BACF108D726D699" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the original publication (
<bibRefCitation id="2C93229AE0FF2F9B25D3B339F34ECDA0" author="Lindley, J" journalOrPublisher=", Leipzig, London, Milano &amp; New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Lindley, J, 1846. New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." title="New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." year="1846">Lindley 1846</bibRefCitation>
) provides no illustration for 
<taxonomicName id="29D3D66CBEDEC022843709E37F93C1D9" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="03B4423C8AEBA27699398D8B817EA0CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="F6A5221109CC831DD5274B56288C6D0B" author="Lindley, J" journalOrPublisher=", Leipzig, London, Milano &amp; New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Lindley, J, 1846. New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." title="New Garden Plant. Edwards's Botanical Register 32: page prior to t. 67." year="1846">Lindley (1846)</bibRefCitation>
mentions that a live specimen was brought from Caraccas and flowered in Syon [Park], London, UK. After searching for specimens that matched these data at K herbarium, we were unable to locate any. We have also searched for a possible unpublished illustration that might serve as the type for 
<taxonomicName id="7506994544CB7754C2B8FC9F9C01D1FC" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="3237D0E1010773D17C456F148B908605" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but were also unsuccessful. Thus, we are currently unable to designate a lectotype for 
<taxonomicName id="747019B3DCAE8823D98CD325DD9CD1F2" genus="X." lsidName="X. giganteum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="giganteum">
<emphasis id="AB1D65458CA49E8078498510C6EC6914" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. giganteum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since this name completely lacks any original material (Art. 9.4., 
<bibRefCitation id="2109624BE3C8E82F9969802669399532" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="The New York Botanical Garden, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B63" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="(2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Since the original description is not enough to undoubtedly apply this name, we also feel it is premature to designate a neotype until natural populations from Caraccas have been studied. Finally, we also choose to tentatively retain it under the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="77E20EE2FDAEC5382E3903988C3C1EF4" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="3606EDAE32762EFAC2C9758126D8B5BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until further information becomes available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77CC31EF807E38F657806B8293AABE1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As explained by 
<bibRefCitation id="E8F8DF14927870DA6890C8100A174C6F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" author="Dorr, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1245 - 1262" refId="B10" refString="Dorr, LJ, Wiersema, JH, 2010. Names of American vascular plants published in Loefling's Iter Hispanicum (1758) and its German translation (1766). Taxon 59 (4): 1245 - 1262, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" title="Names of American vascular plants published in Loefling's Iter Hispanicum (1758) and its German translation (1766)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" volume="59" year="2010">Dorr and Wiersema (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="137003A899EA11C27B7AE90FD4971FFA" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ixia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ixia xiphidium" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiphidium">
<emphasis id="AAD2EDCCC866F29CB077565BDB5C1799" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ixia xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loefl. represents a misinterpretation by 
<bibRefCitation id="C287187090BE6077E4EFE2CE4A4E937E" author="Maas, PJM" journalOrPublisher="Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B27" refString="Maas, PJM, Maas-van de Kamer, H, 1993. Haemodoraceae. Fl. Neotropica 61: 1 - 44" title="Haemodoraceae. Fl." volume="61" year="1993">Maas and Maas-van de Kamer (1993)</bibRefCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="A26EFDFBA7C568CA398CE1068C0B47F4" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">
<normalizedToken id="EBF71ACFAB534B8180AC609D49253C4F" originalValue="Loeflingâs">Loefling's</normalizedToken>
(1758)
</bibRefCitation>
publication. The author never intended to publish a new species but published a new genus, rejecting the application of 
<taxonomicName id="D775EA75A273F2E451A401BF0A2A90EE" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ixia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ixia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AC88B4D3AC73B1497FB8E6D4E0308A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ixia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. for American plants. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="1D9E88BEC652CD5353F52EC9E1F79956" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ixia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ixia xiphidium" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiphidium">
<emphasis id="B72F388DCBB51B5D81F19443ED4DBA1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ixia xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loefl. was never published and should not be included in databases.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02CDBD95F902E36C71809E49E16A612B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
When describing 
<taxonomicName id="052353764E2EEB3E052D7B8A8C840155" genus="X." lsidName="X. rubrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rubrum">
<emphasis id="641A253EF602FBBBFB45A61494ECF8A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rubrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="327446D2F6C5A198236FB51FDD165B6C" author="Don, D" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh New Philosophical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="233 - 244" refId="B9" refString="Don, D, 1832. On the characters and affinities of certain genera in the Flora Peruviana. Edinburgh New Philosophical Journal 13: 233 - 244" title="On the characters and affinities of certain genera in the Flora Peruviana." volume="13" year="1832">Don (1832)</bibRefCitation>
mentions his new species is based on a Ruiz &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="99DA54B003CFF654DB4B2CB3F298E3EF" originalValue="PavÃ³n">Pavon</normalizedToken>
collection, but without indicating a collection number or herbarium information. We came across a specimen matching the protologue with a label in 
<normalizedToken id="CF21B754C31F3C5772D5F4D1A396925C" originalValue="PavÃ³nâs">Pavon's</normalizedToken>
handwriting during a visit to BM, saying, &quot; 
<emphasis id="3D5BBC5D05C9A251158C045E9F68B2D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="5AC43F15932069095025932BA6D88320" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Ornithogalum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ornithogalum rubrum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubrum">Ornithogalum rubrum</taxonomicName>
sp. n.
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="67EBE511537DA47A18FEA4FF773EC734" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Fl. Per.</emphasis>
&quot;. This specimen is here selected as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A57CDFDD564F54E87EDE5CBF49F302E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="22A6EF6B6518F81CDA7B78595140E09C" author="Kuntze, CEO" journalOrPublisher=", Leipzig, London, Milano &amp; New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B23" refString="Kuntze, CEO, 1898. Revisio Generum Plantarum, Vol. 3, part 3. Arthur Felix &amp; al., Leipzig, London, Milano &amp; New York" title="Revisio Generum Plantarum, Vol. 3, part 3. Arthur Felix &amp; al." year="1898">Kuntze (1898)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="74D8D7934A92B77D93C240C5A8A957C6" authority="Willd. ex Baker, 1876" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Eccremis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Viridiplantae" lsidName="Eccremis scabra" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Streptophyta" rank="species" species="scabra">
<emphasis id="A870F0B81D62823A0D718ED585B7B796" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Eccremis scabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a collection from 
<normalizedToken id="1D614BBE8108B6580BBA797361A79EED" originalValue="RÃ­o">Rio</normalizedToken>
Juntas, Bolivia. The author mentions a specimen at B, but we were unable to locate it, and it might have been lost during WWII. Luckily, we were able to locate a duplicate at NY, which is designated here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F32285396CC69B9394106259FDD23EC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D221D28DF3DF5497D4A6A2C0FB901BEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C60551DDC8033267CB691D7DBE9AAD91" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="AE047F4D6FA36849368F85B2EB000BF3" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium caeruleum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="50862B6FA6AB4BCB59C4FDD9AB71C24E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Neotropics, ranging from Mexico, reaching the Antilles, to northern South America (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C426F7461202CFB8016C54A80910DEB6" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="F25" captionText="Figure 25. Distribution of Xiphidium caeruleum Aubl. Beige - Temperate Coniferous Forests and Boreal Forests; Yellow - Temperate Grasslands, Savannahs and Shrublands; Pink - Temperate Broadleaf and Mixed Forests; Light Green - Subtropical Coniferous Forests; Red - Deserts, Xeric Shrublands and Tropical Coniferous Forests; Orange - Tropical / Subtropical Grasslands, Savannahs and Shrublands; Maroon - Dry Broadleaf Forests; Green - Moist Broadleaf Forests; Lilac - Montane Grasslands and Shrublands." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.57996.figure25" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481951" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">25</figureCitation>
). It can be found growing in permanently or seasonally-wet environments, more rarely in dry and rocky environments.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9DC321C2B1BD313B50B31CC6E71260E3" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.57996.figure25" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481951" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 25" startId="F25">
<paragraph id="2E8A5D89D09167EF588D3413006CED26" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="2C3B05F1085FA51C2F9FD7705FB1C725" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 25.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="5403AE53C9655095E29484A9FD6D0C43" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium caeruleum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="B28C2397F25F8915F65DDB63D3636E8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Aubl. Beige - Temperate Coniferous Forests and Boreal Forests; Yellow - Temperate Grasslands, Savannahs and Shrublands; Pink - Temperate Broadleaf and Mixed Forests; Light Green - Subtropical Coniferous Forests; Red - Deserts, Xeric Shrublands and Tropical Coniferous Forests; Orange - Tropical/Subtropical Grasslands, Savannahs and Shrublands; Maroon - Dry Broadleaf Forests; Green - Moist Broadleaf Forests; Lilac - Montane Grasslands and Shrublands.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5A804DF287D7AAB52EB6036DEA6C990" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="022F9F787054A5AD8C4D2146634ED20F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97B6555C4DACC3FAD5EE4C9A34F877DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">It was found in bloom and fruit throughout the year.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF366423C494DA970F83C913EBF50D13" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="249A2BD709651F335983E8A2BFE7D879" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0E1BEB7E22667F0CBC03E19D8157231" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As currently circumscribed, 
<taxonomicName id="D36B1D2D53F8A4F6FBF52F6985E3F6E4" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium caeruleum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="7D96B319A41B9D3F2E8E256E373B045C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed, with equally wide EOO (14,922,959 km2) and AOO (ca. 3,056 km2). Thus, following 
<bibRefCitation id="2B09571103AD7E907CA04B9DDF5A5B18" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" refId="B21" refString="IUCN, 2001. The IUCN Red List Of Threatened Species, version 2010.4. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge U.K. http://www.iucnredlist.org/" title="The IUCN Red List Of Threatened Species, version 2010.4. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge U. K." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" year="2001">
<normalizedToken id="54EF728D72DE684F7058D5436FC55EBC" originalValue="IUCNâs">IUCN's</normalizedToken>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
recommendations, 
<taxonomicName id="FD8EE3C8D9ADC493D5BE7AA4DCFC4BC3" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="13468739F04CCB368FEF95F13AFED399" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as Least Concern (LC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9CCE6FEC880BFC525CABBF64BAACEA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph id="9EE7BC36BCD0FB56986A08EDD4E6D8A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2EA582181C6BC55E7BBB289539C5508E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="320B5D0D2A08F6CB26E3E5EFE12CD34E" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium caeruleum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="CC36A1ED086B8F220BCEA142F06DF5B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widely-distributed species and still a variable taxon even in our present circumscription. Despite our best efforts, we have been unable to correlate any of the observed morphological variability to any of the previously proposed names in 
<taxonomicName id="6535B2DAFD7FB68FD15829AE6AF3C118" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E8C0FCDAC4918C7C8AD89700E006D3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After careful study of protologues, we concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="A45FAC88467EF48218791151D3C33BD5" genus="X." lsidName="X. loeflingii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="loeflingii">
<emphasis id="6733A751C31C058F170D843247B0729D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. loeflingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mutis, 
<taxonomicName id="29F27DE30E3DF9F255CB1393A95313FA" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum subsp. var. var. albidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="variety" species="caeruleum" subSpecies="var." variety="albidum">X. caeruleum var. albidum</taxonomicName>
(Lam.) Backer, 
